snippet: Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan of Turkey has long backed the Syrian rebels. But Turkey shelled rebel positions this week, signaling concern about the dominance of radical Islamist groups.
abstract: Turkey shells rebel positions for first time since Syrian war started; Turkish Prime Min Recep Tayyip Erdogan has effectively kept his country's border with Syria open but Turkey finds itself in same position as many of the rebels’ early backers--concerned that Islamist radicals have come to dominate the ranks of the Syrian opposition.

byline.contributor: Ceylan Yeginsu and Sebnem Arsu contributed reporting from Istanbul, and Alan Cowell from London.

lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan of Turkey has long backed the Syrian rebels. But Turkey shelled rebel positions this week, signaling concern about the dominance of radical Islamist groups.

headline.main: Erdogan, Syrian Rebels’ Leading Ally, Hesitates
headline.print_headline: Syria Rebels’ Leading Ally Hesitates, 31 Months In
